When a TPTP AGR test suite that was developed on TPTP4.2.0 is executed on
TPTP4.2.1 platform, the exception [ org.eclipse.core.runtime.CoreException: Plug-in "org.eclipse.debug.ui" was unable to instantiate class "org.eclipse.debug.internal.ui.views.breakpoints.WorkingSetBreakpointOrganizer"] occurs in the log file(see below for details).

During the execution of the AGR test suite, an eclipse instance appears followed by a series of dialogs with the title "Error parsing the XML file..." and the message "An error occurred while attempting to parse the XML file of the adaptive widget resolver.  See Eclipse log file for more details.  The adaptive widget resolver cannot be used".  

Details of Environment:

Linux SuSE Platform

eclipse-SDK-3.2-linux-gtk.tar.gz
emf-sdo-xsd-SDK-2.2.0.zip
tptp.runtime-TPTP-4.2.1-200607310100.zip
org.eclipse.tptp.test.auto-TPTP-4.2.1-200607310100.zip
